Supporters of the California stem cell measure believe it will accelerate research for diseases like cancer and Alzheimer's.
The proposition, passed by a significant margin, aims to make California a global hub for stem cell research.
The decision bypasses federal restrictions on human embryonic stem cell research.
Meanwhile, Michael J.
Fox endorses John Kerry for supporting stem cell research.
In other health news, exercise shows promise in slowing Parkinson's disease progression.
Scientists also make strides in understanding the genetic basis of Parkinson's, offering hope for future treatments.
